  "text": "All nine strains of rubella virus tested were detected by RT-PCR. No PCR products were generated from the RNAs of 16 other RNA viruses or RNAs from seven cell types and human PBMC DNA. Sequence data (not shown) generated from the nested PCR product from the pharyngeal swab of patient 12 (Table 2) showed 97% homology (62 of 64 bases) with the sequence of the Therien strain of rubella virus [CITATION_1] . No PCR products were generated when reverse transcriptase was omitted from the reverse transcriptase mix (data not shown), indicating that only cDNA was amplified.",
